KW  - Voluntary export restraints
KW  - Anticipation
KW  - Supply constraint
KW  - Video cassette recorders
AB  - This paper investigates the impact of voluntary export restraints (VERs) at the pre-implementation stage when exporters have a good prospect for the VERs. Distinctive features of the VCR market in 1978–86 provide a testable hypothesis to analyze the effect of the EC–Japan VERs, which were implemented in the fiscal years of 1983–85. The paper finds consistent evidence that the VERs affected firms’ pricing behavior in the U.S. market prior to the VER period, as a result of Japanese exporters’ anticipation of the VERs.
